I aspire to take my creative thinking and passion for development and build a fulfilling career in this exciting field.

name: Mitch McCullough
shortQuote: Try to learn to let what is unfair teach you. - DFW
shortAboutMe: While in college as an Industrial & Systems Engineering student, I realized that some of my most enjoyable classes were those which required a certain degree of interaction with a computer. I'd always been interested in new technology growing up, spending hours on the old PC in the family living room until someone had to drag me away. This became even more obvious as I launched into a career as an Operations Industrial Engineer for the Postal Service. I found that I was frequently prone to looking for technical solutions to 'ordinary problems' in data and software. In the end, it was only natural that I found my way to Nashville Software School, where, in familiar company, I can hone my software skills to live out the dream of improving the world one line of code at a time.

name: Micah "Tots" Stotsky
shortQuote: When you only pay attention to your own failures, of course you’re going to put everyone else on a pedestal. You won’t notice that we’re all fucking up too.
shortAboutMe: I like puzzles, games (board and video), anime, and DnD. Straight up nerd to the core.

name: Sariah Campopiano
shortQuote: A smooth sea never made a skilled sailor - Franklin D Roosevelt
shortAboutMe: I am software engineer looking to apply my skills and talents as a full stack developer on an engineering team where I may contribute to projects and refine myself as a software engineer along the way! I have created frontend projects in JavaScript using React and Next JS by myself and as a member of a team of follow developers. I have also created full stack projects using the same frontend tech stack along with Python and Django for the backend also on my own and on a team. I have truly enjoyed my journey becoming a software engineer! I am ready to bring what I've got to the table and be a part of something great!

name: Krima Patel
shortQuote: “Failure is the condiment that gives success its flavor.” - Truman Capote
shortAboutMe: I have been a healthcare worker for over six years and am making a career change into software engineering. My background has allowed me to develop the essential skillsets to transition into the tech field. After college, I was uncertain about my career path, so I continued working in healthcare with an emphasis on new technologies. Having worked with various healthcare applications and machinery has allowed me to see how computers and software programs work together to streamline workflow, resolve issues to ensure accuracy and has shown me just how big of an impact the tech field has had on healthcare. In a matter of a few years it has changed my work experience; this led me to dive into web development courses online which then brought me to Nashville Software School. At NSS, I have gotten experience in problem-solving, working in both individual and team-oriented environments, and overcoming the fear of failure, my biggest challenge. I am eager to learn, grow and maximize my potential as a software engineer. I am excited to be a part of Nashville’s growing tech community!

name: Kukkus Nishaya Maria Raj
shortQuote: "The roots of our success lie in our diverse experiences and the resilience to keep pushing forward."  Unknown author
shortAboutMe: With a background in education and healthcare, I decided to swap textbooks for code and dive into the exciting world of software engineering. My globetrotting adventures to six different countries have given me a wealth of life experiences and a fresh perspective, while my experience working with others has honed my communication and collaboration skills. All in all, I'm ready to bring my unique blend of skills and relentless work ethic to software development and have some fun while solving problems.

name: Brett Hughes
shortQuote:
It's up to the person who's being creative to find ways to emerge and shake up the world of wealth.

shortAboutMe: I am a student of life, always looking to grow my knowledge of subjects I am passionate about.  My first introduction to coding came from a friend who mentioned he was self-taught.  Shocked that you could learn the basics for free online, I began my journey immediately.  Getting laid off from an industry I was truly unhappy in was the catalyst that led me to Nashville Software School.  I value critical thinking over encyclopedic knowledge and inherit curiosity over judgment in everything I do.  My meandering career path gives me a unique perspective that I plan to utilize on my journey.

am a software developer with Object Oriented Programming expirience using JavaScript, React, Pyton, and Django

The software development world has re-ignited a passion for learning that has been the most fun i've had learning new things in almost ten years, which I hope to continue into a fufilling career in software development.
